description: Is this really the end of the road - or is a trade deal just around the corner?
title: Brexit talks: What comes next as negotiators hit pause button?
title_page: Brexit talks: What comes next as negotiators hit pause button? - BBC News
maintext: Cynics might nod their head too when I say that - considering the uncomfortable political compromises both sides have to make to reach a deal - one more "crisis", aka the current stop in talks, is quite useful to demonstrate to the public back home that you're hanging on in there, fighting for their interests.
